article.headline: Lafayette 76, N.J. Tech 57
article.story: NEWARK, N.J. (AP) -- Andrew Brown led all scorers with a career-high 20 points as Lafayette defeated New Jersey Institute of Technology 76-57 Monday night. Brown scored 12 of his points in the second half -- all on 3-pointers -- as Lafayette (3-6) extended a six-point halftime lead by outscoring the Highlanders 40-27 over the final 20 minutes. The Leopards were 9-of-13 on 3-point tries in the second half. Jesper Andersson was the only other double-figure scorer for Lafayette, with 11 points. NJIT (2-6) got 12 points apiece from Kraig Peters and Marc Milbourne Swan. Leading 43-39 with just over 13 minutes to play, Lafayette exploded with a 28-4 run, hitting 8-of-9 3-point tries in the outburst.
